{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f89646a6-c93f-4f27-8f25-29e43706692e","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes affecting your app. Also update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a2162e5-1d84-44b7-910c-0c49fe84d176","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase since they're describing their setup rather than pointing to specific files.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three files they mentioned.","outputTokens":340,"requestId":"D82E:3ED17A:5F3089F:6870F19:69F1626B"},"id":"e98a7a2b-eb7a-4100-8b1f-86fb6125f2aa","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:44:20.472Z","parentId":"f1b619b7-0b50-4fba-afc4-44d1ebd7d58c"}
